summary: The caller is unhappy with the service they have received from an employee of ITC named Andre. The caller was sold items that were not properly billed, and when they asked questions, the employee was rude and dismissive. The caller wants to make a complaint and seeks help in having the issue resolved. They are given a complaint number and informed that a team will call them directly.
speaker_a_summary: The caller, Nim, wants to file a complaint regarding a lack of distributor coverage in their area. Nim is informed that the appropriate team will call them back directly to assist, and provides contact information. The call ends with a confirmation of the complaint number, and a welcome from the representative, Vikram.
speaker_b_summary: The narrator is upset with the behavior of the staff of the provision store owned by Narasimharaja Swami, especially a person named Andre, as during the last two times the narrator visited the store, half the items were not there and Andre was very rude to the narrator. The narrator warns Swami that if the service does not improve, the narrator will take the complain to the higher authorities of the company that supplies the goods to the store. The narrator also gives Swami their contact information.
cohere_points:
- Customer is unhappy with the service they are receiving from an employee at an ITC banana supply store.
- Customer is filing a complaint, and is giving background information about the situation.
- Employee is not billing properly and is rude, and the customer wants this to be rectified.
- Customer is awaiting a call from the MODCON team to take further action.
